clone

protected java.lang.Object clone(boolean copyUUID)
                          throws java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException
This function will return a clone of this object following the general clone() requirement. The difference of this object is to explicit require caller to specify whether to expect a clone object with the same uuid of this object. In other words, if copyUUID is true, the returned clone object will satisfy clone.equals(thisObject) to true; otherwise, the returned clone object will have different uuid value of this object and clone!=thisObject is true, clone.getClass()==thisObject.getClass() is true, but clone.equals(thisObject) will always return false;
